GAMESTATE.achievements: achievements | A boolean array of whether the player has gotten the [achievement](#Achievements) at that index.
GAMESTATE.num_checkpoints_completed: get_num_checkpoints_completed() | Number of tutorials began + number of tutorial ended. Includes tutorials skipped.
GAMESTATE.raining: gg.b.raining | Boolean - currently raining or not.
GAMESTATE.curr_selection_type: gg.inspector.detailed_type | Current selection [inspector content](#InspectorContent) index. (Note that because the game currently (as of 7/25) logs gamestate only after buys, this will always be the type of tile.)
GAMESTATE.curr_selection_data: detailed_data() | SelectFarmbit/SelectItem/SelectTile data, depending on the curr_selection_type.
GAMESTATE.camera_center: prev_center_txty | Tile that the game is currently centered on.
GAMESTATE.gametime: time | Metric to count speed-adjusted time. Based on number of ticks.
GAMESTATE.num_food_produced: num_food_produced | total number of food produced (not bought) since the start of the game |
GAMESTATE.num_milk_produced: num_milk_produced | total number of milk produced (not bought) since the start of the game |
GAMESTATE.num_poop_produced: num_poop_produced | total number of poop produced (not bought) since the start of the game |

STARTGAME.tile_states: tile_states | 2500 element array of tile state indices.
STARTGAME.tile_nutritions: tile_nutritions | 2500 element array of tile nutritions on a scale 0-255.

CHECKPOINT.event_label: arguments[2] | Tutorial name. For example, the name of the tutorial that teaches the player how to build a house is called 'build_a_house'
CHECKPOINT.blurb_history: flush_blurb_history(now) | List of client time relative to now for each blurb popup. (Blurbs are now logged here instead of the [blurb](#blurb) event.)
CHECKPOINT.continue: gg.continue_ls ? 1: 0 | 1/0 boolean to indicate whether the player continued or not
CHECKPOINT.audio: AUDIO ? 1: 0 | 1/0 boolean to indicate whether audio was toggled on or not
CHECKPOINT.fullscreen: g.scenes[1].fullscreen_toggle.on ? 1:  | 1/0 boolean to indicate whether the game was toggled into fullscreen whether or not

SELECTBUY.success: gg.money>=gg.shop.buy_cost(buy) | Boolean. Whether the buy can be selected or not. (Cannot select a buy that cannot be paid for.)

BUY.tile: tile_data_short(gg.b.hover_t) | [Data Short](#DataShort) for the tile the buy will be placed on.
BUY.success: gg.b.placement_valid(gg.b.hover_tgg.shop.selected_buy) | Boolean. Whether the buy can be put on the tile. If not, buy fails.
BUY.buy_hovers: flush_buy_hovers(now) | List of tile [Data Short](#DataShort) appended with client time before now for each hovered tile since either selectbuy log or the previous buy log.

CANCELBUY.buy_hovers: flush_buy_hovers(now) | List of tile [Data Short](#DataShort) appended with client time before now for each hovered tile since either selectbuy log or the previous buy log.

ROADBUILDS.road_builds: flush_road_hovers(now) | List of tile [Data Short](#DataShort) appended with client time before now for each tile a road was built on.

TOGGLENUTRITION.to_state: gg.b.nutrition_view | 1 if nutrition view is being turned on, 0 if turned off.
TOGGLENUTRITION.tile_nutritions: nutrition_array() | 2500 element array of tile nutritions on a scale 0-255.

TOGGLESHOP.shop_open: gg.shop.open | 1 if the shop view is being opened, 0 if closed.

TOGGLEACHIEVEMENTS.achievements_open: gg.achievements.open | 1 if the achievement view is being opened, 0 if closed.

SKIPTUTORIAL.(none): | Event itself indicates that the player skipped a tutorial (the tutorial skipped is the last tutorial event logged).

SPEED.manual: manual_speed_bool | bool: 1 if speed was manually changed, 0 if not

FARMBITDEATH.grave: tile_data_short(f.home) | Tile data short of dead farmbit's home.

BLURB.(none): | Event itself indicates that the player clicked to the next blurb in a tutorial etc. (the tutorial itself is the last tutorial event logged).

RAINSTOPPED.(none): | Log itself indicates that it was raining and the raining has now stopped.

HISTORY.camera_history: flush_camera_history(now) | List of [camera moves](#CameraMove) since last history log.
HISTORY.emote_history: flush_emote_history(now) | List of 11 element sublists [[farmbit](#DataShort), [emote index](#Emotes), time before client_time (negative number)] emotes since last history log.

ENDGAME.(none): | Log itself indicates the player has left the game page. Seperate history and gamestate logs are sent.

aggregate.session_sessionID: X The player's session ID number for this play session
aggregate.session_persistentSessionID: X The session ID for the player's device, persists across multiple players using the same device.
aggregate.session_sessionEventCount: X The total number of events across the entire session
aggregate.sessionDuration: X The total time (in seconds) spent over the entire session

db_columns.app_id: A string identifying which game from which the event came
db_columns.app_id_fast: A second version of the app id, to be removed
db_columns.app_version: The version of the game from which the event came
db_columns.session_id: Unique identifier for the gameplay session
db_columns.persistent_session_id: Unique identifier across all gameplay sessions from a single computer
db_columns.level: The game level in which the event was logged
db_columns.event_custom: A number corresponding to the game-specific event type for events labeled 'Custom'
db_columns.event_data_complex: Data specific to an event type, encoded as a JSON string
db_columns.client_time: The client machine time when the event was generated
db_columns.server_time: The server machine time when the event was logged
db_columns.remote_addr: The IP address for the player's computer
db_columns.req_id: Another ID of some kind, to be removed
db_columns.session_n: Counter of events in the session, from 0. A row with session_n = i is the (i+1)-th event of the session
db_columns.http_user_agent: Data on the type of web browser, OS, etc. in use by the player
